013package org.apache.juneau.http.annotation;
014
015import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.*;
016
017import java.lang.annotation.*;
018
019/**
020 * Swagger contact annotation.
021 *
022 * <p>
023 * The contact information for the exposed API.
024 *
025 * <p>
026 * Used to populate the auto-generated Swagger documentation and UI for server-side <ja>@Rest</ja>-annotated classes.
027 *
028 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
029 * <p class='bjava'>
030 *    <ja>@Swagger</ja>(
031 *       contact=<ja>@Contact</ja>(
032 *          name=<js>"Juneau Development Team"</js>,
033 *          email=<js>"dev@juneau.apache.org"</js>,
034 *          url=<js>"http://juneau.apache.org"</js>
035 *       )
036 *    )
037 * </p>
038 *
039 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
040 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanSwagger2">juneau-bean-swagger-v2</a>
041 *    <li class='extlink'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2#contactObject">Swagger Contact Object</a>
042
043 * </ul>
044 */
045@Documented
046@Retention(RUNTIME)
047public @interface Contact {
048
049    /**
050     * Optional description for the exposed API.
051     *
052     * @return The annotation value.
053     * @since 9.2.0
054     */
055    String[] description() default {};
056
057    /**
058    * <mk>email</mk> field of the <a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2#contactObject">Swagger Contact Object</a>.
059    *
060    * <p>
061    * The email address of the contact person/organization. MUST be in the format of an email address.
062    *
063    * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
064    *    <li class='note'>
065    *       The format is an email string.
066    *    <li class='note'>
067    *       Supports <a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/RestServerSvlVariables">SVL Variables</a> (e.g. <js>"$L{my.localized.variable}"</js>) for the swagger generator.
068    * </ul>
069    *
070    * @return The annotation value.
071    */
072   String email() default "";
073
074   /**
075    * <mk>name</mk> field of the <a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2#contactObject">Swagger Contact Object</a>.
076    *
077    * <p>
078    * The identifying name of the contact person/organization.
079    *
080    * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
081    *    <li class='note'>
082    *       The format is a plain-text string.
083    *    <li class='note'>
084    *       Supports <a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/RestServerSvlVariables">SVL Variables</a> (e.g. <js>"$L{my.localized.variable}"</js>) for the swagger generator.
085    * </ul>
086    *
087    * @return The annotation value.
088    */
089   String name() default "";
090
091   /**
092    * <mk>url</mk> field of the <a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2#contactObject">Swagger Contact Object</a>.
093    *
094    * <p>
095    * The URL pointing to the contact information. MUST be in the format of a URL.
096    *
097    * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
098    *    <li class='note'>
099    *       The format is a URL string.
100    *    <li class='note'>
101    *       Supports <a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/RestServerSvlVariables">SVL Variables</a>
102    *       (e.g. <js>"$L{my.localized.variable}"</js>).
103    * </ul>
104    *
105    * @return The annotation value.
106    */
107   String url() default "";
108}
